Hungary Tax, Wage Rise Impact May Fade in a Year, Simor Says

-- B y   Z o l t a n   S i m o n
-- 
2011-09-29T14:44:48Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-29/hungary-tax-wage-rise-impact-may-fade-in-a-year-simor-says.html
Hungarian government plans to
“significantly” raise the minimum wage next year, on top of
excise and value-added tax increases, will boost inflation
though their impact may fade in a year’s time, central bank
President Andras Simor told a conference in Pecs,  Hungary  today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Zoltan Simon at 
 zsimon@bloomberg.net  